> If I remember correctly, you can't remove the firewall without dropping the
> engine slightly.  Is that true?
>

Depends. On my 73 I was able to pull the firewall and tank with just
the intake manifolds and distributor removed. I don't know what it
would take with a FI engine, but I bet you could just unbolt the
hanger at the frame rails and lower it on a jack enough to get things
clear.


